  "returns": "mindspore.mint.linspacemindspore.mint.linspace(start,end,steps,*,dtype=None)[source]Generate a one-dimensional tensor withstepselements, evenly distributed in the interval [start, end].\\[\\begin{split}\\begin{aligned}\n&step = (end - start)/(steps - 1)\\\\\n&output = [start, start+step, start+2*step, ... , end]\n\\end{aligned}\\end{split}\\]WarningAtlas training series does not support int16 dtype currently.Parametersstart(Union[float,int]) – Start value of interval.end(Union[float,int]) – Last value of interval.steps(int) – Number of elements.Keyword Argumentsdtype(mindspore.dtype,optional) – The data type returned.ReturnsTensorSupported Platforms:AscendExamples>>>importmindspore>>>output=mindspore.mint.linspace(3,10,5)>>>print(output)[ 3.    4.75  6.5   8.25 10.  ]>>>output=mindspore.mint.linspace(-10,10,5)>>>print(output)[-10.  -5.   0.   5.  10.]>>>output=mindspore.mint.linspace(-10,10,1)>>>print(output)[-10.]",
